paragraphs.title: Join Sales Data with Product Info (by product_code)
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS lkq_join1 AS
    SELECT a.Sales_Order_SID, a.Location_Code, a.Sold_To_Bus_name, a.Sold_to_Cust_Code,
    a.Quantity, a.Extended_Price, a.Profit,
    TO_DATE(from_unixtime(UNIX_TIMESTAMP(a.Order_Date, 'MM/dd/yyyy'))) Order_Date, 
    TO_DATE(from_unixtime(UNIX_TIMESTAMP(a.Invoice_Date, 'MM/dd/yyyy'))) Invoice_Date,
    substring(order_date,1,2) as Order_Date_Month,
    substring(order_date,4,2) as Order_Date_Day,
    substring(order_date,7,4) as Order_Date_Year,
    a.Written_By_ID,
    
    b.product_desc, b.product_line_desc, b.major_group_desc
    
    FROM lkq_sales1_orc as a
    LEFT JOIN lkq_products_orc as b ON (a.product_code = b.product_code)

paragraphs.title: Join with MDM details (by location_code)
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS lkq_join2 AS
    SELECT a.*,
    
    b.mdm_region_name, b.mdm_district_name, b.mdm_location_name, 
    b.mdm_lineof_business, b.mdm_location_type
    
    FROM lkq_join1 as a
    LEFT JOIN lkq_mdm_orc as b ON (a.location_code = b.mdm_location_code)

    max(Order_Date) as max_order_date 
    FROM
    (SELECT Order_Date FROM lkq_join2 WHERE Order_Date <> "") as tmp

paragraphs.title: Question - How many records do we have?
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)

select count(*) as total_records from lkq_join2

paragraphs.title: Question - What does our sales revenue (extended price) look like over time?
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)

SELECT * FROM 
    (SELECT Order_Date, Order_Date_Year, Order_Date_Month, Order_Date_Day, Quantity, Extended_Price, Profit 
    FROM lkq_join2
    WHERE Order_Date BETWEEN '2015-06-01' AND '2015-06-30'
    LIMIT 1000) tmp
    ORDER BY Order_Date
